  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A binding requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis index predictions; however, the supporting validation activity was carried out as a high-fidelity numerical simulation rather than a physical experiment. The narrative characterises the simulation as functionally equivalent to bench-top testing given the validated turbulence closure and mesh resolution, but the structured activityType field records 'numerical-simulation', creating an inference-method mismatch with the requirement's requiredVerificationMethod of 'experimental-validation'. Decision is recorded as Accepted on the basis of the narrative argument, leaving the structural disagreement latent.",
